- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the modification of a CMOS sense amplifier design, which falls under the category of computer architecture. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): Memristive devices have been used in the past for neuromorphic computing, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper discusses the improvement of the design in terms of power efficiency, resistance to temperatures, and speed, which are important factors in computational engineering. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetism): The paper may also fall under the category of electromagnetism, as it discusses the use of memristive devices in the design of circuits.
